#-           Military Codes§0
§0
§0PTS = Permission to Speak§0
§0
§0On me! = Get in line behind leader who ordered you§0
§0
§0On my right! = Get on the right of the leader who is commanding you§0
§0
§0Next Page
#- On my left! = Get on the left of the leader who is commanding you§0
§0
§0STS = Shoulder to shoulder with your fellow soldiers in front of the leader§0
§0
§0(You may not speak during training without PTS being granted)§0
§0
§0Next Page
#-      Archer Codes§0
§0    -------------§0
§0
§0Range Arms! = Pull out your bow§0
§0
§0Order Arms! = Put away your weapon§0
§0
§0Make Ready! = Knock an arrow, and draw your bowstring. Wait until told to Fire§0
§0       Next Page
#- Aim! = Find your target before the leader orders you to Fire. Aim only applies when you've made ready§0
§0
§0Blanket fire, 3 sheets! = Fire your bow three times with 3 seconds between each volley§0
§0
§0
§0
§0Next Page
#- Ripple fire from the left! = Soldier on the left side of the line fires, then the soldier to his right, and so on§0
§0
§0Ripple fire from the right! Soldier on the right side of the line fires, the the soldier to his left, and so on§0
§0
§0
§0Next Page
#- Central ripple! = The soldier in the center of the lin fires, then the men to his left and right fire, and the soldier to their left or right fires§0
§0
§0Volley Fire = Every soldier fires one shot at the same time§0
§0
§0
§0Next Page
#- Fire at will! = Fire repeatedly at the enemy until the leader says "Cease fire!"§0
§0
§0Cease him! = Attack the person the leader told you to until they surrender. If they don't, kill them§0
§0
§0
§0
§0Next Page
#- Charge arms! = Archers ready their melee weapon, and charge when the leader says "Charge!"§0
§0
§0Fallback! = Retreat from the battle/enemy§0
§0-------------------     Universal Codes§0
§0   ---------------§0
§0Wear arms! = Take off, or put on armor§0
§0      Next Page
#- Block arms! = Ready your shield§0
§0-------------------     Infantry Code§0
§0   -------------§0
§0Melee arms! = Infantry will draw their swords§0
§0-------------------If there is no leader, you are to battle your own way. There is no §0
§0      Next Page
#- formations, or positions without leaders§0
§0
§0Any orders not mentioned here, or are too complex to write will be explained in training§0
§0
